{"questionId":"9068680","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>When dinitrogen pentoxide, N<sub>2</sub>O<sub>5</sub>, is heated the colourless gas undergoes thermal decomposition to produce brown nitrogen dioxide:</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\">N<sub>2</sub>O<sub>5 </sub>(g) → 2NO<sub>2 </sub>(g) +&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math>O<sub>2 </sub>(g)</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Data for the decomposition at constant temperature is given.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/e34f4af14dfbe176ca1d07eda2950d8a8df752a2.png\"></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Write the rate expression for this reaction.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>rate = <em>k</em>[N<sub>2</sub>O<sub>5</sub>] ✔</p>","meta":{"questionId":"9068680","referenceCode":"21M.2.hl.TZ1.6b(iii)","subjectId":"45-dp-chemistry-last-assessment-2024","title":"Write the rate expression for this reaction.","paper":"2","level":"HL","questionNumber":"b(iii)","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Additional higher level (AHL)","Additional higher level (AHL)","Topic 16: Chemical kinetics","16.1 Rate expression and reaction mechanism","Additional higher level (AHL)","Topic 16: Chemical kinetics"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}